  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Where can I get scholarship for data science in Asia?",
  "response": "There are several universities and organizations in Asia that offer scholarships specifically for data science or related fields. Here are some options you might consider:\n\n### Universities Offering Scholarships in Data Science\n\n1. **National University of Singapore (NUS)**\n   - NUS offers various graduate scholarships, including the NUS Graduate School for Integrative Sciences and Engineering (NGS) Scholarship. Be sure to check their specific programs related to data science.\n\n2. **The University of Tokyo (Japan)**\n   - They offer several scholarships for international students, as well as specific programs in data science and AI.\n\n3. **Tsinghua University (China)**\n   - Tsinghua offers scholarships for its graduate programs, including data science-related courses, with options for international students.\n\n4. **Indian Institutes of Technology (IITs)**\n   - Several IITs offer scholarships for graduate students, especially for those pursuing advanced degrees in computer science and data science.\n\n5. **Korea Advanced Institute of Science and Technology (KAIST)**\n   - KAIST offers scholarships for international students in its graduate programs, which may include data science.\n\n6. **Hong Kong University of Science and Technology (HKUST)**\n   - Scholarships are available for international students applying for postgraduate programs, including those focusing on data science.\n\n### Government and Private Scholarships\n\n1. **Erasmus+ (for Asian countries collaborating with Europe)**\n   - Some programs offer scholarships for students from Asia to study at participating European universities, which may include data science programs.\n\n2. **Commonwealth Shared Scholarships (for study in the UK)**\n   - While this is UK-focused, improved collaborations may offer openings for joint programs in Asia.\n\n3. **Asian Development Bank \u2013 Japan Scholarship Program**\n   - Offers scholarships for students from ADB\u2019s developing member countries to pursue postgraduate studies in selected universities in Asia, including data science.\n\n### Online Search Platforms\n- **Scholarships.com** or **ScholarshipPortal.com**: These online platforms allow you to search for scholarships by field and location.\n\n### Additional Resources\n1. **University Websites**: Always check the financial aid and scholarship sections of university websites for the most accurate and detailed information.\n2. **Social Media & Forums**: Engage in academic forums and social media groups focused on data science in Asia; they may have updated information on scholarships.\n3. **Professional Organizations**: Look into partnerships or scholarships offered by organizations such as IEEE or ACM.\n\n### Tips for Application\n- Prepare a strong statement of purpose and recommendation letters.\n- Highlight any relevant work experience or projects in data science.\n- Apply early and ensure you meet all deadlines.\n\nResearching and applying to several scholarships increases your chances. Good luck!",
